 charge quantization rules fail when the gauge field acquires an\nanomalous dimension. The breakdown of charge quantization is discussed\nextensively in terms of the experimentally measurable modified Aharonov-Bohm\neffect in the strange metal phase of the cuprate superconductors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Apr 2019 18:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Jun 2019 14:03:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 5 Jul 2019 16:20:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-24"}
