ate of 97.6%. The number of sunspots detected by this method\nstrongly agrees with the NOAA catalogue. The sunspot areas calculated by this\nmethod have a 99% correlation with SOHO over the same period, and thus help to\ncalculate the filling factor for wavelength (W.L.) 607nm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Apr 2019 22:41:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-03"}
